      <h1>How to Read Tarot Cards: A Complete Beginner's Guide</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">Tarot cards have been a source of fascination for centuries, but they are frequently misunderstood. Despite what movies and pop culture suggest, tarot is not about predicting the future or communicating with spirits. At its core, tarot is a structured system for self-reflection. The cards provide a framework for examining your thoughts, emotions, and circumstances from angles you might not have considered on your own. Think of a tarot reading less like a crystal ball and more like a focused journaling exercise with visual prompts.</p>
    </header>

